Finally, arguably the pick of the bunch is Andrey Arshavin's hat-trick - because it was actually a quadruple!

In a brilliant 4-4 draw at Anfield in April 2009, Arshavin scored all of Arsenal's goals and crowned one of the all-time great individual performances in Premier League history. 

